article.headline: Bradley 68, Indiana St. 56
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Eddren McCain scored a game-high 14 points to lead Bradley 68-56 over Indiana State on Saturday night. Sam Maniscalco came off the bench and chipped in 11 points and Theron Wilson had 10 points and six rebounds for the Braves (12-8, 6-3 Missouri Valley). Bradley hit 25-of-44 field goal attempts, or about 57 percent. That was compared with just 22-of-55, or 40 percent, for the Sycamores (4-16, 2-7). The Braves, who wore 1985-1986 replica jerseys, led 32-24 at the half in a game which featured five lead changes. Bradley's biggest lead after the half was 19 points with 4:26 remaining. The Sycamores floundered on offense, scoring 16 points in the paint, compared with 28 by the Braves. Rashad Reed had 12 points and Harry Marshall added 11 for Indiana State. Carl Richard had a game-high 12 rebounds.
